Why do we use Automation Testing?

Automation Testing is the process of using software tools (such as Playwright, Selenium, or Cypress) to execute test cases automatically instead of manually.

Benefits of Automation Testing
Saves Time
Executes tests much faster than manual testing.
Hundreds of test cases can run automatically.
Improves Accuracy
Eliminates human errors caused by repetitive testing.
Ensures the same steps are performed consistently every time.
Supports Regression Testing
Quickly verifies that new code changes have not broken existing functionality.
Reusable Test Scripts
Once written, scripts can be executed multiple times with minimal changes.
Cross-Browser Testing
Tests applications across Chrome, Firefox, Edge, and other supported browsers.
CI/CD Integration
Can run automatically whenever code is pushed to a repository using tools like GitHub Actions, Jenkins, or Azure DevOps.
Detailed Reports
Generates logs, screenshots, videos, and HTML reports to help identify failures.

Why do we use Playwright?

Playwright is a modern open-source automation framework developed by OpenAI? No—developed by Microsoft. It is used for automating web browsers and testing web applications.

Advantages of Playwright
1. Cross-Browser Support

Playwright works with:

Chromium (Google Chrome, Microsoft Edge)
Firefox
WebKit (Safari engine)
2. Cross-Platform Support

Runs on:

Windows
macOS
Linux
3. Multiple Programming Languages

Supports:

JavaScript
TypeScript
Python
Java
C#
4. Fast Execution
Faster than many traditional automation frameworks.
Can execute tests in parallel.
5. Auto Waiting

Playwright automatically waits for elements to become ready before interacting with them, reducing the need for explicit waits.

6. Multiple Tabs and Windows

Handles multiple browser tabs and pop-up windows easily.

7. API Testing

Can send API requests directly using Playwright's request features.

8. Built-in Features

Includes:

Screenshots
Video recording
Trace viewer
HTML reports
Network interception